Known Issues

Some modules are not compiled by autodoc, therefor may not documented. The issue comes from the fact that while compiling, the environment that the doc is compiled in, has to have the required packages used in the documented code. Not having them installed results in an empty doc page.

If one wants to rebuild the html via ./docs./make.bat html make sure to have the required packages used in the source code!

Other errors include missing files and bad indexing. Examples:

  • FileNotFoundError: [Errno 2] No such file or directory: './input_data/input_source_original.parquet'.

  • FileNotFoundError: [Errno 2] No such file or directory: 'gizmo_logo.png'.

  • TypeError: 'type' object is not subscriptable.

Full error message in ./docs/logs/log_11_06_2024_1303_manual.txt
